## CRITICAL NOTES

Temperature constraint: when thinking is enabled (adaptive or deep),
do NOT pass temperature to the API. Anthropic requires temperature=1
(the default) for thinking mode. Passing any temperature value
causes an API error. The buildThinkingConfig function handles this
by omitting temperature entirely.

budget_tokens vs max_tokens: max_tokens must always be greater than
budget_tokens. The resolveMaxTokens function enforces this.
For deep mode (budget=16000), max_tokens must be at least 16001 —
set to 20000 to give room for the actual response after thinking.

Claude 4 thinking is summarized by default: the thinking content
in API responses for Opus 4.6 and Sonnet 4.6 is a summary of the
internal reasoning, not the raw stream. This is still highly useful
for showing users why choices were made. It streams token by token
so the UX feels responsive. The ThinkingBlock component handles
both streaming (dots animation) and complete (expandable) states.

Adaptive thinking on simple requests: when thinkingMode='adaptive'
and the user asks something simple like "change the color to blue",
Claude will skip thinking entirely and the thinking_start event
will never fire. The ThinkingBlock simply won't appear. This is
correct behavior — don't add a fallback message like "no reasoning
needed", just show nothing.

Tool use + thinking: the Anthropic API supports extended thinking
with tool use. tool_choice must be 'auto' or 'none' — never force
a specific tool when thinking is enabled. The agent tools are all
configured with auto tool choice so this works without changes.

Conversation history: thinking blocks from previous turns are
automatically ignored by the Anthropic API when building context.
You do NOT need to filter them out of the history array you send.
The API handles this internally.
```